Third—Kitcheposkissegan (by Papasainse), from Point Grondine west- ward, six miles inland, by two miles in front, so as to include the small Lake N essinassung—a tract for themselves and their bands.

Fourth—Wabakekik, three miles front, near Shebawenaning, by ﬁve miles inland, for himself and band.

Eleventh—Tagawinini and his band, two miles square at Wanabitibing, a place about forty miles inland, near Lake Nipissing.

Twelfth—Keokouse and his band, four miles front from Thessalon River eastward, by four miles inland.
